rdf:Description.lla:note: Fined two days pay for being asleep under the long boat while on lookout duty, while at sea. (1871-05-25)
Taken ill while at sea off Cape Vincent, with sickness and dysentery. Various treatments applied, including castor oil and 10 grains of some sort of poison, "according to medical guide".
Fined two days pay for being asleep on duty while at Ibraila (=Braila, Romania).
Deserted ship on 1872-04-01 taking all his effects, at Zarate, Buenos Aires
